lenders.occupational_info:
Jean Claude Frajmund is the Founder and CEO of ECO Shrimp Garden, an indoor-urban farm producing a fresh and eco-friendly shrimp in the Hudson Valley.

A former communication technology consultant and filmmaker, Jean-Claude started ECO Shrimp Garden one year ago, with the belief that it’s possible to feed the world without threatening the environment and endangering human health. 

The idea of producing and selling fresh shrimp to the local market is not new to Jean-Claude. When he was 16 years old, in the ’80s, after spending a month of vacation working with fishermen in the north of Brazil, Jean-Claude planned to open an inland shrimp farm. But at that time there wasn’t technology available that could allow him to produce shrimps in cold climates, in harmony with the environment.   He had to wait some decades to finally, in the beginning of 2014, find in the pages of The New York Times an article talking about a new technology. 

After months of research, conversations with aquaculture experts and shrimp farmers, market analysis and tons of “spreadsheets and calculations “, Jean-Claude was convinced that producing sustainable shrimp, using an environmentally conscientious production approach, and selling it fresh to local customers was now possible. 

Jean’s commitment to a more ethical and responsible farming practices was determinant in the decision of starting the new business. 
“Local and environmental conscious business are a powerful agent for meaningful change in our community and planet.” 

Jean-Claude and his wife, Jaqueline, have two children: Chloe and Leon.
